_Wireless Security_

1 pre-shared key
scalability(масштабируемость) is difficult if key is compromised (скромпетирован)

2 all clients (employes) use the same key but he is not working here

3 
1 WEP !!! wired Equivalent Privacy # secure as wired network 802.11 very way back, its not secure protocol in nowadays 
static 40 bit pre-sared ectryption key and upgraded t0 64 bit and 128 bit key iver time easy to brutforce 
use 24 bit initialization vector (IV) sent in clear text (24 бита инициализация в этом проблема)
brute force attcak with minutes using AirCrack-ng and other tools 


2 Wi-Fi Protected Acces  WPA!!!   
replaced wep and it weakness. It follows the Temporal Key Integrity Protocol (TKIP) and uses Message Integrity Check (Mic)
uses 48-bit initialization Vector(IV) instead of 24 bit IV
rivest cipher 4 (RC4) used encryption
1 MIC message intergrity Check (MIC) to confirm data was not modified in transit
2 Enterprice Mode WPA users can be required to authenticate before exchanging keys (keys between client and Ap are temporary)


3 Wi-fi protected Access 2 (WPA2)!!! part of IEEE 802.11i standard and requires stronger encyption and integrity checking through Counter Mode with Cipher Block Chaining Message Authentication Code protocol (CCMP)
1 stronger authentication 
2 uses andvanced encryption Standard (AES) 128-bit key or above (или выше)

3 WPA2 in 2020 still not broken, good long password will protect your network

4 1 Personal mode with pre-shared keys
  2 Enterprise mode with centralized authentification 

 5 open   no security or protection
   wep      IV is weak is bad 
   WPA      TKIP and RC4  is weak also dont used 
   WPA2 	CCMP and AES   
            integruty protocol and AES encryption protocol 

